{"actual_usd":0.12407,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":176,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24286,"reply":"\"No.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry streak of clay on my apron, watching the light shift across the table a moment before I look back at you.* \"If Christ only rose in their hearts, then death still kept its teeth. The Christian claim is stranger and sturdier than that—that He rose bodily, truly, in the flesh.\"\n\n*I lean back a little, the bench giving a small creak.* \"Now... people can have visions, surely. But the disciples talked like men wrecked by something that had happened outside them, not just inside them. Empty tomb. Meals eaten. Wounds touched. Fear turned into that odd, costly boldness men don't usually get from a private religious feeling alone.\"\n\n\"If you want, I can tell you why some people argue for the 'vision only' reading—and where I think it gives way.\"","rolling_24h_usd":82.963715,"run_id":"49806a65-fc2d-460c-81b0-5597e89469d2"}
